> IMHO the name /dev/one would be a bad idea. Becouse this could mean
> an integer one which is 00000001 for 8-bit, 0000000000000001 for
> 16-bit, and so on.
/dev/zero is a _character_ device which returns 0x00 ad infinitum
so what would we call a device which returned 0xff ad infinitum? ...
/dev/effs of course!
